tomatically loading\nthese modules.  after that, lighttpd will fail to start up if\nauth.backend requires one of these modules and the module is not loaded.\n\n(the purpose of this change is to remove from the lighttpd core server\n the dependencies on ldap or mariadb libraries.)','configfile.c','1237','291','17','0','false','false','false','2016-10-21 18:20:02-04:00'),('lighttpd','1.4.40','fa67918d3e4955932becf4579c69914d2be0798f','Glenn Strauss','fix fastcgi, scgi, proxy reconnect on failure\n\nfactor modules for consistent code flow for reconnect on failure','mod_fastcgi.c','2417','552','64','159','true','true','false','2016-10-25 20:30:17-04:00'),('lighttpd','1.4.40','fa67918d3e4955932becf4579c69914d2be0798f','Glenn Strauss','fix fastcgi, scgi, proxy reconnect on failure\n\nfactor modules for consistent code flow for reconnect on failure','mod_proxy.c','934','224','214','256','true','true','false','2016-10-25 20:30:17-04:00'),('lighttpd','1.4.40','fa67918d3e4955932becf4579c69914d2be0798f','Glenn Strauss','fix fastcgi, scgi, proxy reconnect on failure\n\nfactor modules for consistent code flow for reconnect on failure','mod_scgi.c','1963','463','75','111','true','true','false','2016-10-25 20:30:17-04:00'),('lighttpd','1.4.40','b2ab1c8d0eadf3b85bf5a777bc8cb59ae5277cb8','Glenn Strauss','[core] network_open_file_chunk() temp file opt\n\nnetwork_open_file_chunk() temp file optimization:\nskip file size checks if file is temp file created by lighttpd\n\nif not temp file, always fstat() for file size check instead of\nusing potentially out-of-date info from stat_cache\n\nx-ref:\n  https://redmine.lighttpd.net/boards/3/topics/6884','network_write_no_mmap.c','102','32','12','18','false','false','false','2016-10-25 23:36:06-04:00'),('lighttpd','1.4.40','86c68ecbc7e8f10551fefd5b97b2345f2ed571b2','Glenn Strauss','[mod_rewrite] add more info in error log msg\n\nadd more info in endless loop error log msg\n\nx-ref:\n  https://redmine.lighttpd.net/boards/2/topics/6899','mod_rewrite.c','346','77','3','2','true','false','false','2016-10-26 11:47:06-04:00'),('lighttpd','1.4.40','eb37615a47de85a53909225706cb9240652c704a','Glenn Strauss','[core] fix fd leak when using libev (fixes #2761)\n\nserver.event-handler = \"libev\" would leak fds after the change made\nin commit:40f16d5 since fdevent_libev.c:fdevent_libev_poll() always\nreturned 0 ready events after handling the event callbacks itself.\ntherefore, fdevent_libev.c:fdevent_libev_poll() must also call\nfdevent_sched_run() to handled fds scheduled to be closed.\n\nthis bug was introduced in 1.4.42.\n\n(thx mittwinter for troubleshooting and identifying problem)\n\nnote: server.event-handler = \"libev\" is no longer recommended.\nlighttpd provides event handlers optimized for modern systems for most\nplatforms, and the limited way that lighttpd uses libev does not provide\nany advantages over the os-specific optimized event handlers.\n\nx-ref:\n  \"fd leak with libev in 1.4.42\"\n  https://redmine.lighttpd.net/issues/2761','fdevent_libev.c','125','29','5','2','true','false','false','2016-10-29 09:13:49-04:00'),('lighttpd','1.4.40','23503883babccc578ddde4a5b9a4a6d2cd020320','Glenn Strauss','[core] fix potential streaming tempfile corruption (fixes #2760)\n\nset o_append after mkstemp() in chunk.c  (mkostemp() is not as portable)\n(also set fd_cloexec to avoid potentially leaking open tempfiles to cgi)\n\n(thx dieter.ro for helping track this down)\n\nx-ref:\n  https://redmine.lighttpd.net/boards/3/topics/6884\n  \"potential tempfile corruption when streaming response\"\n  https://redmine.lighttpd.net/issues/2760','chunk.c','522','134','3','0','true','false','false','2016-10-29 09:14:07-04:00'),('lighttpd','1.4.40','204df0681400da072116633b1d4368e6aa900d13','Glenn Strauss','minor: coverity comments','chunk.c','522','134','1','0','false','false','false','2016-10-29 09:14:07-04:00'),('lighttpd','1.4.40','204df0681400da072116633b1d4368e6aa900d13','Glenn Strauss','minor: coverity comments','mod_